\f0\b \cf0 Increasing memory\

\f1\b0 The PCGen Mac build is set to use up to 256mb of memory space but if you load a large number of datasets or if you run into problems outputting PDF's you may want to increase the amount used. To access this setting right click or control-click the PCGen.app and selecting "Show Package Contents" from the resulting menu. Find the Info.plist file in the Contents folder. Find the line which reads "-Xms128m -Xmx256m", this is the line which sets the memory usage, you can change it to "-Xms256m -Xmx512m" to double the memory.\
